Major tanker operator Japan Line Ltd&lt;JLIT.T> said it will raise seven billion yen by issuing 63.66mln shares at 110 yen each to help reduce debt and restoreprofitability within two years.    Half of the sum raised will be returned to creditor bankswhich in December were asked to temporarily waive part of theirloan repayments, it said.    The other half will be used to bolster operations hit bythe yen's steep appreciation and the global shipping slump, thecompany added. MORE&#3;